<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 21 at 1:44AM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Lake Effect Snow Showers Early This Morning...
Lake effect snow showers will continue across northern Lake and
northern Porter counties early this morning. There may be some
localized snowfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches, especially for areas
near the lake. Untreated surfaces will likely become snow covered
and slippery. Motorists should reduce speed and allow extra
traveling distance.</description>
